<content type="html" xml:base="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/viewtopic.php?t=2892&amp;p=13684#p13684"><![CDATA[
@rambomhtri, try this button. I think at 125% DPI and size 0, it should exactly match the Windows 8.1 original button dimensions and sharpness. That said, what I guessed above was right. Windows 8.1 internally switches to a different image when you increase the DPI, it doesn't scale the image. I suspect it has Start button images in its DLLs all the way up to 500% DPI. Even at smaller sizes/100% DPI it doesn't downscale a larger image. Unscaled image=higher quality if you want pixel perfect sharpness.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://www.classicshell.net/forum/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=54">Gaurav</a> — Tue Jul 01, 2014 4:07 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
</entry>
